```csharp
public static void QuickSort(int[] arr, int left, int right)
{
    if (left < right)
    {
        int pivotIndex = Partition(arr, left, right);
        QuickSort(arr, left, pivotIndex - 1);
        QuickSort(arr, pivotIndex + 1, right);
    }
}

public static int Partition(int[] arr, int left, int right)
{
    int pivot = arr[right];
    int i = left - 1;

    for (int j = left; j < right; j++)
    {
        if (arr[j] < pivot)
        {
            i++;
            Swap(arr, i, j);
        }
    }

    Swap(arr, i + 1, right);
    return i + 1;
}

public static void Swap(int[] arr, int i, int j)
{
    int temp = arr[i];
    arr[i] = arr[j];
    arr[j] = temp;
}

public static void Main()
{
    int[] arr = { 10, 80, 30, 90, 40, 50, 70 };
    QuickSort(arr, 0, arr.Length - 1);
    Console.WriteLine(string.Join(", ", arr));
}
```

In this code, the `QuickSort` method takes the array, left index and right index as input and recursively sorts the array using the quicksort algorithm. The `Partition` method chooses a pivot element and partitions the array into two subarrays. The `Swap` method swaps two elements in the array. The `Main` method initializes the array, calls the `QuickSort` method and prints the sorted array.

